text: welcome to the tribeca grill.  our award winning wine list is arranged by grape variety and then
region.  the list is international with a focus on burgundy, california and the rhône.  many vertical
listings of california wines have come directly from the producers.
our châteauneuf du pape selection is the largest in the world.  we feel these wines are among the
best values in the market today.  often produced from old, low yielding vines, the wines have
concentrated and complex flavors that complement the robust cuisine that tribeca grill is known
we have many rare wines in our collection.  they include magnificent aged white and red
burgundy, red bordeaux and rhône wines.  the best of the best are featured in our ‘wines of the
century,’ something to consider on a special occasion.
all of our wines are kept in temperature-controlled cellars at 58 degrees.  some, including most red
wines, may need a few minutes to warm up in the glass once they are opened.  we have the utmost
confidence in our suppliers of these wines, however they are presented in “as is” condition.  please
understand that there can be bottle variation with wines that have been aged for long periods of
white half bottles and large formats

text: In 1967, Aimé Sabon returned from his military service. He promptly set himself to tending the grapes
that his father had been selling to the local co-operative and to bottling the wine that his father-in-
law had been selling to a negociant (a merchant of bulk wine). The Domaine was named after the
historic vineyard "La Janasse" in Courthezon– the sandy northeastern quadrant of the appelation in
Châteauneuf du Pape where Chateau Rayas alike produces elegant grenache dominant wines. Now
under the responsibility of the next generation, brother sister team Christophe and Isabelle, Domaine
de la Janasse produces wines of exemplary freshness with purity of fruit, refined texture and intensely
complex aromas. Their estate bottling is a classic blend of hand-picked and hand-sorted grenache,
syrah and mourvedre. As is the 'Vieilles Vignes' or 'Old Vine' cuvée which issues from centenarian
vines while the exquisite 'Chaupin' features exclusively old-vine grenache. Finally, we are fortunate to
present the very rare 'Cuvee XXL,' as monumental a wine as any to come out of the region.
